1
00:00:42,626 --> 00:00:43,651
[This drama is a work of fiction.]

2
00:00:43,651 --> 00:00:44,690
[Any resemblance to real persons,
places, or events is coincidental.]

3
00:00:44,690 --> 00:00:45,712
[Scenes with child actors and animals
were filmed safely]

4
00:00:45,712 --> 00:00:47,447
[under professional supervision.]

5
00:00:47,447 --> 00:00:49,549
[Episode 8]

6
00:00:49,549 --> 00:00:51,510
<i>Bang Tae Seop is gaining fast,</i>

7
00:00:51,510 --> 00:00:53,803
[Bang Tae Seop goes all in for final push]
<i>hot on Park Hong Jip's heels.</i>

8
00:00:53,803 --> 00:00:56,042
<i>Park Hong Jip holds 31.6%,</i>

9
00:00:56,042 --> 00:00:58,475
<i>Bang Tae Seop sits at 29.7%.</i>

10
00:00:58,475 --> 00:01:01,561
<i>With the Dongnam-gap race tightening,</i>

11
00:01:01,561 --> 00:01:03,730
<i>a growing number of polls forecast</i>

12
00:01:03,730 --> 00:01:05,816
[Chu's boost narrows race to margin of error]
<i>a win for Bang Tae Seop,</i>

13
00:01:05,816 --> 00:01:08,527
<i>and voters across the district
are up for grabs.</i>

14
00:01:08,527 --> 00:01:11,250
<i>Park's side is fighting to defend its lead,</i>

15
00:01:11,250 --> 00:01:13,834
<i>while Bang's team says momentum has shifted</i>

16
00:01:13,834 --> 00:01:16,876
<i>and goes on the attack.</i>

17
00:01:18,770 --> 00:01:20,375
Every stock that's been falling apart

18
00:01:20,375 --> 00:01:23,508
bounces right back once you let it go.

19
00:01:27,390 --> 00:01:29,722
He keeps crossing my mind.

20
00:01:30,590 --> 00:01:32,558
Bang Tae Seop.

21
00:01:34,918 --> 00:01:37,396
Bang Tae Seop.

22
00:01:38,724 --> 00:01:40,774
[From Bang Tae Seop, Sir]

23
00:01:42,644 --> 00:01:45,083
Is someone watching me?

24
00:01:45,083 --> 00:01:47,441
Did someone put a camera in here or something?

25
00:01:47,441 --> 00:01:49,211
[Sir, here's an update on Lee Yang Mi]

26
00:01:57,701 --> 00:02:00,753
What is she pulling this time?

27
00:02:03,457 --> 00:02:06,126
[Bang Tae Seop]

28
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:09,250
Bang Tae Seop...

29
00:02:09,250 --> 00:02:11,558
No.

30
00:02:11,558 --> 00:02:12,938
Absolutely not.

31
00:02:12,938 --> 00:02:14,602
If I reach out first, I lose.

32
00:02:18,292 --> 00:02:21,482
I was reckless back then.

33
00:02:24,918 --> 00:02:27,029
What is this?

34
00:02:33,053 --> 00:02:35,663
I do regret it.

35
00:02:36,823 --> 00:02:39,500
As you should.

36
00:02:39,500 --> 00:02:42,712
Trust me, I already do.

37
00:02:59,986 --> 00:03:03,746
Lee Yang Mi's up to something lately.

38
00:03:03,746 --> 00:03:05,395
You're really going to let that slide?

39
00:03:05,395 --> 00:03:07,406
Not a chance.

40
00:03:07,406 --> 00:03:11,108
That's why I'm teaming up with you
to bring her down.

41
00:03:11,108 --> 00:03:15,036
I've got all the paperwork you requested.

42
00:03:16,167 --> 00:03:19,125
That movie Lee Yang Mi's producing,

43
00:03:19,125 --> 00:03:21,336
it's budgeted at 30 billion won,

44
00:03:21,336 --> 00:03:24,459
but actual production spending

45
00:03:24,459 --> 00:03:25,993
comes in below 10 billion.

46
00:03:25,993 --> 00:03:28,000
So 20 billion just vanishes.

47
00:03:28,000 --> 00:03:31,761
That's Son Guk Won's slush fund money, right?

48
00:03:34,500 --> 00:03:36,550
With the presidency coming up,

49
00:03:36,550 --> 00:03:39,500
she's using the movie to clean cash?

50
00:03:39,500 --> 00:03:41,521
Exactly.

51
00:03:42,597 --> 00:03:46,435
One word of this hits the press, it's over.

52
00:03:46,435 --> 00:03:48,854
She chose Sang Ah
since there's no risk to her own people,

53
00:03:48,854 --> 00:03:50,792
and made her the sacrificial lamb.

54
00:03:50,792 --> 00:03:53,950
We use this to strike Lee Yang Mi first.

55
00:04:03,994 --> 00:04:06,663
Don't touch the film.

56
00:04:06,663 --> 00:04:07,667
Why not?

57
00:04:07,667 --> 00:04:11,736
Sang Ah catches shrapnel from that, too.

58
00:04:11,736 --> 00:04:14,963
Knowing the inside story is enough.

59
00:04:14,963 --> 00:04:17,925
We need something big enough to cover it.

60
00:04:20,093 --> 00:04:22,095
For now,

61
00:04:22,095 --> 00:04:25,098
arrange a sit-down with Assemblyman Choi.

62
00:04:25,098 --> 00:04:27,692
Assemblyman Choi? No problem.

63
00:04:33,542 --> 00:04:35,943
There's...

64
00:04:35,943 --> 00:04:39,870
something I've been working on quietly.

65
00:04:44,910 --> 00:04:46,828
Okay.

66
00:04:50,083 --> 00:04:52,842
The dust. Seriously.

67
00:04:53,459 --> 00:04:55,882
This dust is killing me.

68
00:05:03,792 --> 00:05:05,667
This isn't an abduction, right?

69
00:05:05,667 --> 00:05:07,940
What would I even do with you?

70
00:05:10,894 --> 00:05:12,980
The death of the Daeyang Fund CEO, Yoon,

71
00:05:12,980 --> 00:05:16,690
who built Son Guk Won's slush fund.

72
00:05:16,690 --> 00:05:21,488
That's always been Son Guk Won's weak spot.

73
00:05:21,488 --> 00:05:23,375
The party threw everything at it,

74
00:05:23,375 --> 00:05:26,876
but never found a way in.

75
00:05:30,834 --> 00:05:32,541
The day CEO Yoon was set

76
00:05:32,541 --> 00:05:34,710
to meet a reporter to expose Son Guk Won,

77
00:05:34,710 --> 00:05:36,753
he died in a car wreck.

78
00:05:36,753 --> 00:05:39,173
It was written off as sudden acceleration,

79
00:05:39,173 --> 00:05:41,952
but everyone suspected he was killed.

80
00:05:41,952 --> 00:05:44,167
Word was, there's someone called "the Shadow"

81
00:05:44,167 --> 00:05:47,573
doing all of Son Guk Won's dirty work.

82
00:05:47,573 --> 00:05:50,167
Right, we went after the Shadow ourselves,

83
00:05:50,167 --> 00:05:51,602
and came up empty.

84
00:05:51,602 --> 00:05:54,250
Here's the thing.

85
00:05:54,250 --> 00:05:56,481
We tracked him down.

86
00:05:56,481 --> 00:05:58,150
For real?

87
00:05:58,150 --> 00:05:59,583
This is Shadow intel

88
00:05:59,583 --> 00:06:02,028
from a senior prosecutor who dug

89
00:06:02,028 --> 00:06:04,614
into Son Guk Won at the time.

90
00:06:04,614 --> 00:06:07,792
[Evidence of Suspect Park Jae Hyun's
Illegal Transactions Uncovered]

91
00:06:08,500 --> 00:06:12,332
This individual
works as Son Guk Won's aide right now.

92
00:06:12,332 --> 00:06:14,374
This guy is the Shadow?

93
00:06:14,374 --> 00:06:16,884
98% sure.

94
00:06:19,334 --> 00:06:21,256
99%.

95
00:06:21,256 --> 00:06:24,906
The Shadow's exit records overlap

96
00:06:24,906 --> 00:06:28,597
with slush money routed to offshore accounts

97
00:06:28,597 --> 00:06:31,042
that dropped off the radar.

98
00:06:31,042 --> 00:06:34,644
That proves the Shadow works for Son Guk Won.

99
00:06:34,644 --> 00:06:37,083
So we frame the Shadow

100
00:06:37,083 --> 00:06:39,732
as the one behind CEO Yoon's death

101
00:06:39,732 --> 00:06:43,417
and pry open the Daeyang Fund slush.

102
00:06:43,417 --> 00:06:44,446
Now,

103
00:06:44,446 --> 00:06:48,959
if Bang hands that to the Changjo Party,

104
00:06:48,959 --> 00:06:51,119
the presidential race is already won.

105
00:06:51,119 --> 00:06:54,422
Naturally, that deserves something in return.

106
00:06:55,498 --> 00:06:58,634
As long as the source is solid, fine.

107
00:07:00,337 --> 00:07:01,880
For the general election,

108
00:07:01,880 --> 00:07:03,465
the party's full support

109
00:07:03,465 --> 00:07:06,667
plus Assemblyman Gu's rally appearances.
And then...

110
00:07:06,667 --> 00:07:08,637
I want a guarantee

111
00:07:08,637 --> 00:07:12,148
for the Chief of Staff position
in your camp for the next run.

112
00:07:17,125 --> 00:07:20,295
Why are you being so small-time?

113
00:07:20,295 --> 00:07:23,451
- Guess you don't want the intel.
- No.

114
00:07:27,292 --> 00:07:29,331
Done.

115
00:07:41,375 --> 00:07:44,930
Do me a favor before you retire.

116
00:07:47,217 --> 00:07:51,138
Step one, we convince the Shadow
that Son Guk Won sold him out.

117
00:07:51,138 --> 00:07:53,375
Splitting Son Guk Won

118
00:07:53,375 --> 00:07:56,768
and the Shadow apart, that's on you.

119
00:07:56,768 --> 00:07:58,635
[Son Guk Won:
Jae Hyun's been my shadow for a long time]

120
00:07:58,635 --> 00:08:00,740
[I've entrusted him with many tasks]

121
00:08:03,167 --> 00:08:04,950
By the way,

122
00:08:05,860 --> 00:08:10,435
how did you know I was drafting my resignation?

123
00:08:10,435 --> 00:08:12,534
You told me if they skipped you again,

124
00:08:12,534 --> 00:08:15,503
you'd walk away from the prosecution.

125
00:08:16,579 --> 00:08:17,914
[Assemblyman Choi Hak Sun]

126
00:08:17,914 --> 00:08:21,342
Pay him a visit. He'll give you a position.

127
00:08:25,250 --> 00:08:27,681
Okay.

128
00:08:32,595 --> 00:08:35,307
Just like old times.

129
00:08:55,959 --> 00:08:58,379
Hello.

130
00:09:00,456 --> 00:09:04,448
So, you're the legendary Shadow.

131
00:09:04,448 --> 00:09:07,221
What a pleasure to finally meet you.

132
00:09:17,292 --> 00:09:19,560
Once we pull forensics

133
00:09:19,560 --> 00:09:22,187
off the victim's phone, it all comes to light.

134
00:09:22,187 --> 00:09:24,655
So why don't we cut to it?

135
00:09:24,655 --> 00:09:27,334
We can prove you were on the phone

136
00:09:27,334 --> 00:09:30,619
with CEO Yoon just before his death.

137
00:09:32,781 --> 00:09:35,101
I have no idea what you're talking about.

138
00:09:35,101 --> 00:09:37,415
What's your point here?

139
00:09:37,415 --> 00:09:41,331
Forensics, whatever you want, be my guest.

140
00:09:41,331 --> 00:09:43,250
None of you

141
00:09:43,250 --> 00:09:45,801
can lay a finger on me.

142
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:53,423
This time might be different.

143
00:09:53,423 --> 00:09:55,811
The person who gave you up?

144
00:09:58,417 --> 00:10:01,108
Came from your own side.

145
00:10:02,103 --> 00:10:04,698
The proof was strong enough

146
00:10:04,698 --> 00:10:08,616
to justify picking you up on the spot.

147
00:10:11,611 --> 00:10:13,992
[Assemblyman Son Guk Won]

148
00:10:19,039 --> 00:10:23,756
This guy keeps calling. So annoying.

149
00:10:41,534 --> 00:10:45,027
Calling Son Guk Won would be a mistake.

150
00:10:47,617 --> 00:10:49,292
Son Guk Won

151
00:10:49,292 --> 00:10:51,700
already cut you loose.

152
00:10:55,281 --> 00:10:56,792
You all

153
00:10:56,792 --> 00:10:59,876
have no idea who Assemblyman Son is.

154
00:10:59,876 --> 00:11:03,114
He'd never discard me this way.

155
00:11:03,114 --> 00:11:05,707
He'd have me killed.

156
00:11:05,707 --> 00:11:07,501
It's not the same this time.

157
00:11:07,501 --> 00:11:10,753
If I were him, with a presidential run ahead,

158
00:11:10,753 --> 00:11:13,082
I'd clean house with people like you

159
00:11:13,082 --> 00:11:16,759
who know where the bodies are buried.

160
00:11:16,759 --> 00:11:19,292
That locks down the presidency

161
00:11:19,292 --> 00:11:21,025
and the whole time in office,

162
00:11:21,025 --> 00:11:23,899
with nobody holding anything over him.

163
00:11:29,626 --> 00:11:36,597
The second Son Guk Won
rose as a contender, he was ready to drop you.

164
00:11:36,597 --> 00:11:39,959
CEO Yoon's accident, the timing was right,

165
00:11:39,959 --> 00:11:43,377
so he fed you to the prosecutors.

166
00:11:46,396 --> 00:11:49,130
Enough with the fairy tales.

167
00:11:49,130 --> 00:11:51,424
Keep playing loyal, then.

168
00:11:51,424 --> 00:11:54,876
You'll be the devoted mutt who saw it coming

169
00:11:54,876 --> 00:11:58,861
and still obeyed, only to get tossed aside,

170
00:11:58,861 --> 00:12:00,584
left to rot behind bars

171
00:12:00,584 --> 00:12:02,980
for the rest of your days.

172
00:12:07,936 --> 00:12:09,875
Look.

173
00:12:09,875 --> 00:12:11,981
The only way you walk out of here is

174
00:12:11,981 --> 00:12:15,936
if you turn over every piece of evidence.

175
00:12:15,936 --> 00:12:18,591
Son Guk Won takes the fall,

176
00:12:18,591 --> 00:12:22,750
gets a proper investigation.
That's your only move.

177
00:12:25,913 --> 00:12:29,750
If you had hard evidence I murdered CEO Yoon,

178
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:31,848
you'd have come straight at me.

179
00:12:31,848 --> 00:12:33,626
None of these back-channel tactics

180
00:12:33,626 --> 00:12:37,549
would've been necessary, right?

181
00:12:37,549 --> 00:12:40,225
So what that tells me is,

182
00:12:41,530 --> 00:12:44,146
you're holding an empty hand.

183
00:12:48,083 --> 00:12:49,443
Well?

184
00:12:49,443 --> 00:12:51,361
Am I off the mark?

185
00:12:59,167 --> 00:13:01,330
Hey.

186
00:13:03,125 --> 00:13:06,811
This is my final offer

187
00:13:06,811 --> 00:13:09,463
to keep you alive.

188
00:13:14,834 --> 00:13:18,191
It's your call.

189
00:13:18,191 --> 00:13:20,959
And everything that follows,

190
00:13:20,959 --> 00:13:23,435
that's on you, too.

191
00:13:50,288 --> 00:13:52,077
<i>A new chapter for Dongnam-gap.</i>

192
00:13:52,077 --> 00:13:55,251
<i>Cast your vote for Bang Tae Seop.</i>

193
00:13:55,251 --> 00:13:58,417
[Gu Hong Seo, campaign chair,
stumps for Bang Tae Seop]

194
00:13:58,417 --> 00:13:59,923
<i>- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!</i>

195
00:13:59,923 --> 00:14:01,876
<i>- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!</i>

196
00:14:01,876 --> 00:14:03,509
<i>- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!</i>

197
00:14:03,509 --> 00:14:05,386
<i>- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!</i>

198
00:14:05,386 --> 00:14:08,685
[Changjo Party eyes first win]
<i>- Bang Tae Seop! - Bang Tae Seop!</i>

199
00:14:08,685 --> 00:14:12,648
[over Doyak in Dongnam-gap]
<i>- Bang Tae Seop! - Bang Tae Seop!</i>

200
00:14:14,375 --> 00:14:16,238
This way.

201
00:14:21,819 --> 00:14:25,039
[Full Script Reading and Production Ritual
for Four Seasons]

202
00:14:27,709 --> 00:14:29,960
Over here.

203
00:14:38,167 --> 00:14:40,470
Hello.

204
00:14:46,385 --> 00:14:48,270
- Hello.
- Hello.

205
00:14:48,270 --> 00:14:50,397
Thank you for making the trip.

206
00:14:53,542 --> 00:14:54,936
Why isn't she here yet?

207
00:14:54,936 --> 00:14:57,689
I've been trying to reach her.

208
00:14:57,689 --> 00:14:59,899
[Four Seasons, Hwang Jeong Won as Yu Hwa]
Are you sure you gave her the exact time?

209
00:14:59,899 --> 00:15:01,700
Yes, I am.

210
00:15:02,292 --> 00:15:04,453
But why would she...

211
00:15:56,834 --> 00:16:00,884
Now that we're all present,
let's start the read-through.

212
00:16:07,751 --> 00:16:10,584
There's an intimate scene
scheduled for the first day,

213
00:16:10,584 --> 00:16:12,691
which I realize is uncomfortable
for both of you,

214
00:16:12,691 --> 00:16:14,140
but the director thinks, emotionally,

215
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:16,375
that rawness actually plays better on screen,

216
00:16:16,375 --> 00:16:19,444
so moving things around
wasn't really an option.

217
00:16:21,042 --> 00:16:23,115
It's fine by me.

218
00:16:30,782 --> 00:16:32,874
You're okay with it, right?

219
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:49,349
I asked if you're okay.

220
00:16:51,667 --> 00:16:54,938
Well, I'm not.

221
00:17:01,042 --> 00:17:03,606
Did the director get lost?

222
00:17:03,606 --> 00:17:07,075
I'll step out for a second.

223
00:17:18,816 --> 00:17:20,797
Want a drink?

224
00:17:30,834 --> 00:17:33,101
How have you been?

225
00:17:35,500 --> 00:17:37,898
What about you, senior?

226
00:17:45,626 --> 00:17:47,657
Senior?

227
00:18:03,012 --> 00:18:06,031
Once that whole thing was over,

228
00:18:06,031 --> 00:18:09,046
I vanished, and you could breathe again.

229
00:18:09,046 --> 00:18:11,209
But now that I'm back,

230
00:18:11,209 --> 00:18:13,433
I guess it's hitting you.

231
00:18:26,083 --> 00:18:28,417
Yeah.

232
00:18:28,417 --> 00:18:30,659
It does hit different.

233
00:18:35,917 --> 00:18:38,917
I knew you'd show up someday,

234
00:18:41,692 --> 00:18:44,464
just didn't expect it to be like this.

235
00:18:55,292 --> 00:18:58,478
You were the one who wanted to work together.

236
00:19:24,039 --> 00:19:25,839
Tell me,

237
00:19:27,136 --> 00:19:30,260
what's your connection to Director Lee?

238
00:19:39,345 --> 00:19:42,542
What did she offer you

239
00:19:42,542 --> 00:19:45,817
to put you in this movie?

240
00:19:50,209 --> 00:19:53,633
What am I even capable of?

241
00:19:53,633 --> 00:19:55,785
You know who I am.

242
00:19:56,500 --> 00:19:58,580
And you know where I come from.

243
00:20:08,165 --> 00:20:10,167
[Case Summary Report]

244
00:20:10,167 --> 00:20:11,716
[Hwang Jeong Won fatally stabbed Yoon Chul Ho]

245
00:20:11,716 --> 00:20:13,441
[in the abdomen in a serious violent crime]

246
00:20:20,594 --> 00:20:24,542
[Crime Scene Photo, Exhibit No. 1]

247
00:20:24,542 --> 00:20:27,589
[Suspect Hwang confessed to the crime
immediately after her arrest]

248
00:20:52,626 --> 00:20:54,630
Chu Sang Ah...

249
00:20:59,918 --> 00:21:01,768
Ms. Chu...

250
00:21:05,292 --> 00:21:09,150
The same way you played
Park Jae Sang seven years ago,

251
00:21:09,804 --> 00:21:12,696
were you putting on a show for me, too?

252
00:21:18,542 --> 00:21:21,329
You were hoping I'd do

253
00:21:22,950 --> 00:21:25,750
exactly what he did, weren't you?

254
00:21:40,000 --> 00:21:41,787
I'm sorry.

255
00:21:41,787 --> 00:21:43,727
I'm so sorry.

256
00:22:19,590 --> 00:22:21,709
I've already briefed the Director,

257
00:22:21,709 --> 00:22:23,667
so just move forward with the plan.

258
00:22:23,667 --> 00:22:25,761
Yeah.

259
00:22:25,761 --> 00:22:28,556
Director, this is a late visit...

260
00:22:28,556 --> 00:22:30,389
First day on set, right?

261
00:22:30,389 --> 00:22:32,227
I'm here to cheer on the actors.

262
00:22:32,227 --> 00:22:33,602
That means a lot.

263
00:22:33,602 --> 00:22:36,148
- Everyone's doing well.
- Thanks.

264
00:23:04,306 --> 00:23:06,500
Ready.

265
00:23:06,500 --> 00:23:08,436
Action!

266
00:24:55,579 --> 00:24:57,247
Cut.

267
00:24:58,539 --> 00:25:00,082
Okay.

268
00:25:00,082 --> 00:25:03,378
That's good. Moving on to the next setup.

269
00:25:09,626 --> 00:25:12,584
That's solid material right there.

270
00:25:12,584 --> 00:25:13,972
Nice job, everybody.

271
00:25:13,972 --> 00:25:15,308
Strong first day.

272
00:25:15,308 --> 00:25:17,542
We've got a winner on our hands.

273
00:25:17,542 --> 00:25:19,102
Set up a nice gathering

274
00:25:19,102 --> 00:25:21,334
- and give the actors some praise.
- Sure.

275
00:25:21,334 --> 00:25:23,459
If there's anything you need,
just say the word.

276
00:25:23,459 --> 00:25:25,490
- You're doing great.
- Thank you.

277
00:25:32,614 --> 00:25:34,283
Well, if it isn't candidate Bang!

278
00:25:34,283 --> 00:25:36,410
Stopping by for your wife, as busy as you are.

279
00:25:36,410 --> 00:25:38,956
Thank you all for the hard work.

280
00:25:45,626 --> 00:25:47,209
Everything all right?

281
00:25:47,209 --> 00:25:49,466
Yeah.

282
00:25:49,466 --> 00:25:51,349
Hwang Jeong Won?

283
00:25:56,209 --> 00:25:58,398
Nice to meet you.

284
00:26:04,911 --> 00:26:07,150
Yes, nice to meet you as well.

285
00:26:07,150 --> 00:26:10,871
I've read about you and heard quite a bit.

286
00:26:10,871 --> 00:26:14,205
Same here. Your name comes up often.

287
00:26:15,791 --> 00:26:17,709
Please take care of...

288
00:26:18,959 --> 00:26:21,588
my wife on set.

289
00:26:25,792 --> 00:26:27,969
Of course.

290
00:26:32,841 --> 00:26:34,667
You must be cold.

291
00:26:34,667 --> 00:26:36,216
Yeah.

292
00:26:36,972 --> 00:26:39,397
How sweet.

293
00:26:50,876 --> 00:26:52,613
I'm turning down

294
00:26:52,613 --> 00:26:55,072
your offer.

295
00:26:55,072 --> 00:26:57,798
Where's all this confidence coming from?

296
00:26:57,798 --> 00:27:00,829
Whatever you've been doing, I told you.

297
00:27:00,829 --> 00:27:05,011
The higher you go, the worse the crash.

298
00:27:05,011 --> 00:27:07,675
You have a safety net lined up?

299
00:27:10,281 --> 00:27:12,646
Give it time, and you'll find out.

300
00:27:18,626 --> 00:27:20,641
Then again,

301
00:27:20,641 --> 00:27:24,525
a man who betrayed his own wife
will never change.

302
00:27:27,142 --> 00:27:30,317
Back in your prosecutor days,

303
00:27:30,317 --> 00:27:32,736
that legal fight
over Sang Ah's agency contract.

304
00:27:32,736 --> 00:27:34,611
What does that have to do with anything?

305
00:27:34,611 --> 00:27:35,739
You're the one who engineered that.

306
00:27:35,739 --> 00:27:37,062
All right.

307
00:27:37,062 --> 00:27:40,092
I set up the tax evasion leak, sure.

308
00:27:40,092 --> 00:27:42,326
But I looked into it,

309
00:27:42,326 --> 00:27:44,957
and you were aware of it all along.

310
00:27:44,957 --> 00:27:46,455
The Chief Prosecutor

311
00:27:46,455 --> 00:27:48,812
promised to promote you if you buried it,

312
00:27:48,812 --> 00:27:51,295
so you just swept it under the rug, right?

313
00:27:51,295 --> 00:27:53,090
Careful what you say.

314
00:27:53,090 --> 00:27:56,176
I stepped aside
because I had no way to fight you then.

315
00:27:56,176 --> 00:27:58,588
The game has changed.

316
00:27:58,588 --> 00:28:04,016
This time I've got a hand you can't beat.

317
00:28:04,016 --> 00:28:05,858
Is that so?

318
00:28:09,910 --> 00:28:13,533
You have no clue what cards I'm sitting on,

319
00:28:14,959 --> 00:28:16,391
and you're calling for a showdown?

320
00:28:16,391 --> 00:28:18,709
What's with you?

321
00:28:18,709 --> 00:28:20,200
Getting cold feet?

322
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:22,792
If you're so sure, lay them on the table.

323
00:28:26,330 --> 00:28:29,668
I expected a tiger,

324
00:28:30,470 --> 00:28:33,797
but all I got was a stray pup.

325
00:28:33,797 --> 00:28:34,965
The general election,

326
00:28:34,965 --> 00:28:39,142
and Sang Ah's movie. Keep your hands off both.

327
00:29:11,124 --> 00:29:13,011
[Bang Tae Seop]

328
00:29:20,387 --> 00:29:22,810
Want to grab a drink?

329
00:29:38,000 --> 00:29:40,703
Come here.

330
00:29:41,792 --> 00:29:43,949
These are the people you'll be running with,

331
00:29:43,949 --> 00:29:45,445
[Changjo Party]
so get acquainted.

332
00:29:45,445 --> 00:29:47,661
Guan Yu, Zhang Fei, Zhuge Liang,
the whole crew's here.

333
00:29:47,661 --> 00:29:49,790
Good to meet you all.

334
00:29:49,790 --> 00:29:52,374
Sit down, please.

335
00:29:52,374 --> 00:29:53,667
- Get him a glass.
- Right away.

336
00:29:53,667 --> 00:29:55,352
- This is a sure thing, right?
- Absolutely.

337
00:29:57,089 --> 00:29:58,893
Thank you.

338
00:29:59,589 --> 00:30:00,757
Let's all have a drink.

339
00:30:00,757 --> 00:30:03,853
- Well done.
- Well done.

340
00:30:06,555 --> 00:30:09,083
We've got great energy.
Everything's going to work out.

341
00:30:09,083 --> 00:30:11,353
<i>Seoam's Dongnam-gap continues
to be a fierce contest,</i>

342
00:30:11,353 --> 00:30:13,820
<i>with the outcome hanging by a thread.</i>

343
00:30:13,820 --> 00:30:15,964
<i>The latest survey results reveal</i>

344
00:30:15,964 --> 00:30:19,444
<i>only a 0.6-point spread</i>

345
00:30:19,444 --> 00:30:22,466
<i>separating the leading two candidates.</i>

346
00:30:22,466 --> 00:30:26,285
[Seoam Dongnam-gap Poll Summary]
<i>Doyak's Park Hong Jip stands at 32.2%,</i>

347
00:30:26,285 --> 00:30:27,918
<i>while Changjo's Bang Tae Seop</i>

348
00:30:27,918 --> 00:30:29,703
[Park Hong Jip, Bang Tae Seop]
<i>comes in at 32.8%,</i>

349
00:30:29,703 --> 00:30:31,417
<i>edging past Park Hong Jip</i>

350
00:30:31,417 --> 00:30:35,800
<i>in a contest that could go either way.</i>

351
00:30:47,763 --> 00:30:52,726
After 30 years of defeat in this district,

352
00:30:52,726 --> 00:30:55,194
the unthinkable has happened.

353
00:30:56,751 --> 00:30:59,900
Bang Tae Seop has at last

354
00:30:59,900 --> 00:31:04,579
surpassed the Doyak Party in Dongnam-gap.

355
00:31:06,490 --> 00:31:08,160
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!

356
00:31:08,160 --> 00:31:09,661
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!

357
00:31:09,661 --> 00:31:11,961
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!

358
00:31:13,240 --> 00:31:15,125
Thank you all!

359
00:31:15,125 --> 00:31:18,545
I'll carry this energy and write a new chapter!

360
00:31:18,545 --> 00:31:22,722
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

361
00:31:31,390 --> 00:31:33,323
[Unknown Caller]

362
00:31:35,125 --> 00:31:39,439
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!

363
00:31:39,439 --> 00:31:43,111
- Bang Tae Seop!
- Bang Tae Seop!

364
00:31:45,910 --> 00:31:48,998
<i>You wrecked a person's life,
and you're living large.</i>

365
00:31:54,125 --> 00:31:57,010
You're the prick who hung
around Hwang Jeong Won, right?

366
00:31:57,010 --> 00:32:00,959
<i>You pulled her into this in the first place.</i>

367
00:32:00,959 --> 00:32:03,846
<i>If something goes wrong,
you're the first one I deal with.</i>

368
00:32:04,842 --> 00:32:07,516
Start with what's going on.

369
00:32:09,626 --> 00:32:11,709
Hwang Jeong Won

370
00:32:11,709 --> 00:32:14,817
got trapped because of the Park Jae Sang case.

371
00:32:14,817 --> 00:32:17,060
The casting, everything, it was all a sham.

372
00:32:17,060 --> 00:32:18,897
She walked right into a trap.

373
00:32:18,897 --> 00:32:22,734
Enough. Who has leverage on her,
and what is it?

374
00:32:22,734 --> 00:32:25,785
Spit it out, you piece of shit.

375
00:32:27,542 --> 00:32:28,957
Hey, hello?

376
00:32:28,957 --> 00:32:30,748
Hello?

377
00:33:40,330 --> 00:33:43,696
What was Bang Tae Seop to you?

378
00:33:53,626 --> 00:33:56,751
He was someone I owed a great deal to.

379
00:33:59,417 --> 00:34:01,589
Someone you owed a great deal to...

380
00:34:07,042 --> 00:34:08,846
Right.

381
00:34:09,820 --> 00:34:12,933
Even if we've ended up here,

382
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:16,228
he and I both,

383
00:34:18,042 --> 00:34:21,275
we may have once been good people.

384
00:34:26,859 --> 00:34:30,493
Let me give you the answer

385
00:34:31,667 --> 00:34:33,621
to what you asked me then.

386
00:34:39,095 --> 00:34:42,213
When it came to Park Jae Sang, yeah...

387
00:34:43,626 --> 00:34:46,361
those feelings were real.

388
00:34:46,361 --> 00:34:51,222
To get away from the ones
who ruined me and my friend,

389
00:34:52,792 --> 00:34:54,959
I turned into something monstrous

390
00:34:54,959 --> 00:34:57,478
that devoured someone else.

391
00:35:06,090 --> 00:35:07,709
I believed if I suffered enough for it,

392
00:35:07,709 --> 00:35:11,402
I could finally get out.

393
00:35:11,402 --> 00:35:15,830
But when he caught up with me again,
I understood

394
00:35:17,250 --> 00:35:20,126
the only way out was death.

395
00:35:27,042 --> 00:35:29,343
That's the reason.

396
00:35:36,444 --> 00:35:39,805
If anyone discovered me,

397
00:35:39,805 --> 00:35:42,565
I hoped it wouldn't be Bang Tae Seop.

398
00:35:45,125 --> 00:35:47,653
I wished it'd be you instead.

399
00:35:55,751 --> 00:35:57,857
That's everything.

400
00:35:57,857 --> 00:36:00,499
Not sure that's the answer
you were looking for.

401
00:36:03,709 --> 00:36:05,671
Either way,

402
00:36:06,500 --> 00:36:09,091
no matter what my reasons were,

403
00:36:09,890 --> 00:36:12,748
I was only thinking of myself.

404
00:36:12,748 --> 00:36:14,722
I'm sorry.

405
00:36:18,792 --> 00:36:20,737
The reason I brought it up was

406
00:36:21,370 --> 00:36:25,232
I was afraid you were still blaming yourself.

407
00:36:28,000 --> 00:36:31,125
I chose to go there on my own,

408
00:36:31,125 --> 00:36:33,542
and I needed you to hear

409
00:36:33,542 --> 00:36:36,035
that none of it is on you.

410
00:36:59,667 --> 00:37:02,102
I'm sure this isn't news to you,

411
00:37:06,638 --> 00:37:09,652
but I went to kill Park Jae Sang.

412
00:37:34,709 --> 00:37:37,054
I need to use the restroom, give me a second.

413
00:40:28,635 --> 00:40:30,511
[Bang Tae Seop]

414
00:40:30,511 --> 00:40:34,106
[Find Sang Ah's location.
I'm asking if you found her]

415
00:40:37,143 --> 00:40:40,404
[Recents]

416
00:41:10,751 --> 00:41:12,978
<i>Shit!</i>

417
00:41:13,682 --> 00:41:15,856
<i>This is fun.</i>

418
00:41:18,395 --> 00:41:20,211
<i>It's fun.</i>

419
00:41:20,211 --> 00:41:21,666
<i>Why did you kill him?</i>

420
00:41:22,689 --> 00:41:24,521
<i>Park Jae Sang.</i>

421
00:41:31,918 --> 00:41:34,124
<i>It wasn't me.</i>

422
00:41:35,370 --> 00:41:37,961
<i>But the way things stand,</i>

423
00:41:41,531 --> 00:41:44,468
<i>maybe it needs to be you who killed him.</i>

424
00:43:16,969 --> 00:43:20,309
For me, Bang Tae Seop

425
00:43:20,309 --> 00:43:22,751
is more than a husband. He's my ally.

426
00:43:22,751 --> 00:43:24,818
He's my family.

427
00:43:25,414 --> 00:43:28,296
My father passed when I was little,

428
00:43:28,296 --> 00:43:32,028
and I was raised by a fierce single mom,

429
00:43:32,028 --> 00:43:36,026
so the meaning of family
and warmth was lost on me.

430
00:43:36,026 --> 00:43:38,918
He never stopped having faith in me,

431
00:43:38,918 --> 00:43:40,834
stayed right beside me,

432
00:43:40,834 --> 00:43:44,023
and rooted for me. Knowing that kind of bond,

433
00:43:44,023 --> 00:43:47,059
he's the one who taught me what that means

434
00:43:47,059 --> 00:43:49,509
for my life.

435
00:43:51,107 --> 00:43:52,584
So,

436
00:43:52,584 --> 00:43:57,809
what does your wife mean to you?

437
00:44:04,083 --> 00:44:06,136
Right from our very first meeting,

438
00:44:06,136 --> 00:44:10,152
I sensed something familiar in her.

439
00:44:10,152 --> 00:44:11,858
As our conversations deepened,

440
00:44:11,858 --> 00:44:14,819
I had this instinct that together,

441
00:44:14,819 --> 00:44:16,459
we could support one another

442
00:44:16,459 --> 00:44:20,398
through whatever came our way.

443
00:44:20,398 --> 00:44:22,243
If she hadn't been there,

444
00:44:22,243 --> 00:44:25,573
I wouldn't be the man standing here today.

445
00:44:25,573 --> 00:44:28,663
<i>Though they once faced a scandal-fueled crisis,</i>

446
00:44:28,663 --> 00:44:31,169
<i>the pair's united front through hardship</i>

447
00:44:31,169 --> 00:44:33,296
<i>has been a major factor
driving his approval ratings.</i>

448
00:44:33,296 --> 00:44:36,340
<i>This wave of support
has deepened public confidence in Bang</i>

449
00:44:36,340 --> 00:44:38,667
[Turning Crisis into Opportunity]
<i>and appears to have cemented the arrival</i>

450
00:44:38,667 --> 00:44:40,764
[Bang Tae Seop Leads in Dongnam-gap]
<i>of the rising political force, Bang Tae Seop.</i>

451
00:44:40,764 --> 00:44:42,680
<i>Unless something unexpected occurs,</i>

452
00:44:42,680 --> 00:44:45,899
<i>this race appears to be Bang Tae Seop's to win.</i>

453
00:44:52,459 --> 00:44:55,404
Rushing here right after work,
you must be beat.

454
00:44:55,404 --> 00:44:57,411
How about a beer?

455
00:44:58,709 --> 00:45:00,987
I'm shooting tomorrow.

456
00:45:00,987 --> 00:45:03,250
I'm wiped out. I'm turning in.

457
00:46:06,517 --> 00:46:11,068
Why Hwang Jeong Won disappeared
after the Park Jae Sang case...

458
00:46:13,709 --> 00:46:15,906
<i>What's going on?</i>

459
00:46:15,906 --> 00:46:19,726
<i>If I don't do what they say,
they pin Park Jae Sang on me.</i>

460
00:46:19,726 --> 00:46:22,746
<i>One more murder rap, and it's over for me.</i>

461
00:46:26,959 --> 00:46:30,058
Lee Yang Mi has dirt on her
and is pulling her strings.

462
00:46:31,750 --> 00:46:33,006
So?

463
00:46:33,006 --> 00:46:36,718
Do you have a read on how this is playing out?

464
00:46:37,919 --> 00:46:40,373
Do I have to spell it all out for you?

465
00:46:40,373 --> 00:46:43,467
Choi Ji Ho coming and going
from the set bugs me.

466
00:46:43,467 --> 00:46:47,020
So now that I've told you this much,
do something about it.

467
00:46:56,483 --> 00:46:59,167
The election's the day after tomorrow.

468
00:46:59,167 --> 00:47:01,701
Can you clean this up after it blows?

469
00:47:38,898 --> 00:47:40,694
Have you lost your mind?

470
00:47:40,694 --> 00:47:42,951
What the hell do you want from me?

471
00:47:46,334 --> 00:47:48,665
I've missed you.

472
00:47:51,876 --> 00:47:54,229
Since that day,

473
00:47:54,229 --> 00:47:57,257
I haven't gone one day without thinking of you.

474
00:47:58,780 --> 00:48:01,216
That night,

475
00:48:01,216 --> 00:48:04,514
if you believed I felt something for you,

476
00:48:06,125 --> 00:48:08,518
that was in your head.

477
00:48:12,348 --> 00:48:15,432
I was in pain, and I wasn't thinking straight,

478
00:48:15,432 --> 00:48:18,236
and all I wanted was someone to hold on to.

479
00:48:21,709 --> 00:48:24,284
Don't you want to break free?

480
00:48:26,834 --> 00:48:29,831
How much longer can you keep this up?

481
00:48:44,508 --> 00:48:47,349
Sorry, Director.

482
00:48:48,387 --> 00:48:50,709
End of roll.

483
00:48:50,709 --> 00:48:52,854
27, 10, 3.

484
00:48:57,417 --> 00:48:59,722
Are you feeling okay?

485
00:48:59,722 --> 00:49:02,656
I'm lightheaded. Give me a minute.

486
00:49:03,602 --> 00:49:05,334
- You all right?
- Let's take a quick break

487
00:49:05,334 --> 00:49:07,827
- and then get back to it.
- Are you okay?

488
00:49:27,092 --> 00:49:29,473
<i>Your wife's routine has been normal.</i>

489
00:49:29,473 --> 00:49:31,719
<i>With your ratings going up,
WR looks like they're</i>

490
00:49:31,719 --> 00:49:35,167
<i>doubling down on her commercials
and the movie press.</i>

491
00:49:35,167 --> 00:49:36,982
Understood.

492
00:49:43,898 --> 00:49:48,974
[Major Buzz: Sang Ah and Newcomer Jeong Won
to Star in "Four Seasons."]

493
00:49:53,250 --> 00:49:56,914
<i>Why Hwang Jeong Won disappeared
after the Park Jae Sang case...</i>

494
00:49:56,914 --> 00:50:00,338
<i>Lee Yang Mi has dirt on her
and is pulling her strings.</i>

495
00:50:07,709 --> 00:50:11,262
<i>Whatever you've been doing, I told you.</i>

496
00:50:11,262 --> 00:50:15,228
<i>The higher you go, the worse the crash.</i>

497
00:50:23,062 --> 00:50:24,125
Damn it.

498
00:50:24,125 --> 00:50:27,240
I can smell Lee Yang Mi all over this.

499
00:50:27,878 --> 00:50:30,611
I'm losing my mind over this.

500
00:50:30,611 --> 00:50:33,838
She's building up to something.

501
00:50:33,838 --> 00:50:37,918
Choi Ji Ho moving around
all of a sudden is shady, too.

502
00:50:37,918 --> 00:50:40,599
It feels like she's ready to hit Chu Sang Ah

503
00:50:40,599 --> 00:50:43,631
timed to the general election.

504
00:50:48,006 --> 00:50:50,968
Do we know when Lee Yang Mi plans to strike?

505
00:50:50,968 --> 00:50:52,198
Word from her inner circle is

506
00:50:52,198 --> 00:50:55,597
she's set to drop it on election day.

507
00:50:55,597 --> 00:50:57,460
Sang Ah may be the target,

508
00:50:57,460 --> 00:50:59,939
but I'm the one she's really after.

509
00:51:00,834 --> 00:51:03,433
She's trying to knock me out of the race

510
00:51:04,126 --> 00:51:08,198
so Son Guk Won can use me
as a shield through the presidential run.

511
00:51:09,240 --> 00:51:12,202
What about reaching out to Assemblyman Choi?

512
00:51:13,834 --> 00:51:16,701
The party isn't about to put itself on the line

513
00:51:16,701 --> 00:51:19,376
by taking on that level of exposure for me.

514
00:51:25,473 --> 00:51:27,876
If this election doesn't go my way,

515
00:51:27,876 --> 00:51:31,930
they'll milk the Shadow intel I handed over

516
00:51:32,985 --> 00:51:35,751
and throw me out.

517
00:51:35,751 --> 00:51:37,918
I'll get dropped without a second thought.

518
00:51:37,918 --> 00:51:40,230
Damn.

519
00:51:45,480 --> 00:51:46,979
If that's how Lee Yang Mi wants to play it,

520
00:51:46,979 --> 00:51:49,948
then I'm forced to take her on directly.

